!import-table-item --BackStory_FamilyPowerStructure --Unorganized. Your family has no internal organization. Family members are responsible for their own actions. --10 --
!import-table-item --BackStory_FamilyPowerStructure --Elders. The oldest members control your family. --20 --
!import-table-item --BackStory_FamilyPowerStructure --Patriarchy. The male members control your family. --10 --
!import-table-item --BackStory_FamilyPowerStructure --Matriarchy. The female members control your family. --10 --
!import-table-item --BackStory_FamilyPowerStructure --Oligarchy. The richest members control your family. --10 --
!import-table-item --BackStory_FamilyPowerStructure --Meritocracy. The members with the most talent (usually ability in the family business) control your family. --10 --
!import-table-item --BackStory_FamilyPowerStructure --Divided. One branch of the family follows one leadership structure, and one or more others follow a different structure. --10 --
!import-table-item --BackStory_FamilyPowerStructure --External. Your family is lead by an outsider; liege lord or other person to whom the family has sworn support. --5 --
!import-table-item --BackStory_FamilyPowerStructure --Domination. A violent or dangerous family member rules your family through fear. --5 --
